540
00:38:24,970 --> 00:38:26,120
But she shot Khun Phra

541
00:38:27,920 --> 00:38:30,110
because of what he did, right?

542
00:38:31,510 --> 00:38:34,810
Forcing Lady Nuanlaor to marry him.

543
00:38:35,970 --> 00:38:37,380
Raping Champi.

544
00:38:37,800 --> 00:38:40,660
And neglecting Lady Rampueng
and their child.

545
00:38:41,450 --> 00:38:43,080
All that said,

546
00:38:44,160 --> 00:38:46,550
he easily tops the chart

547
00:38:47,380 --> 00:38:48,870
of the worst man ever.

548
00:38:53,080 --> 00:38:54,090
Yeah.

549
00:38:54,910 --> 00:38:56,500
I feel sorry for Champi, too.

550
00:38:59,100 --> 00:39:00,440
She's a slave like us,

551
00:39:01,560 --> 00:39:04,940
loyal and so protective
of her master.

552
00:39:07,410 --> 00:39:09,050
She didn't mean to frame you.

553
00:39:14,350 --> 00:39:15,500
But if she confessed,

554
00:39:15,820 --> 00:39:17,980
Lady Nuanlaor would've
been implicated.

555
00:39:19,160 --> 00:39:20,500
She had no choice.

556
00:39:22,280 --> 00:39:23,290
Look.

557
00:39:24,900 --> 00:39:29,230
I get why you two
feel sorry for her.

558
00:39:29,580 --> 00:39:32,030
I feel bad for what Khun Phra
did to her, too.

559
00:39:32,700 --> 00:39:33,730
But in the end,

560
00:39:34,390 --> 00:39:37,440
Champi was the one who shot him.

561
00:39:37,880 --> 00:39:38,980
It is a fact.

562
00:39:39,400 --> 00:39:41,550
She did it for a reason.

563
00:39:49,450 --> 00:39:52,700
I wish there was
a better way to judge her.

564
00:39:53,780 --> 00:39:55,900
The voice of the accused
should be heard.

565
00:39:56,130 --> 00:39:59,070
Let the arguments
or reasons be heard.

566
00:40:00,440 --> 00:40:03,650
Not just rush into execution,

567
00:40:03,780 --> 00:40:05,650
an eye for an eye, like this.

568
00:40:07,090 --> 00:40:08,380
Think about it.

569
00:40:08,590 --> 00:40:12,220
Thongbai almost died for nothing.

570
00:40:12,770 --> 00:40:14,710
The gun fell into his hand.

571
00:40:15,350 --> 00:40:16,500
Is that fair?

572
00:40:17,940 --> 00:40:19,390
Of course not.

573
00:40:19,850 --> 00:40:20,990
But what can we do?

574
00:40:21,190 --> 00:40:21,680
Hmm?

575
00:40:21,940 --> 00:40:24,140
Champi's going to be executed
no matter what.

576
00:40:24,240 --> 00:40:25,530
Hard as we might,

577
00:40:25,570 --> 00:40:28,250
slaves like us
can't change the system.

578
00:40:29,310 --> 00:40:30,690
Hrr.

579
00:40:32,620 --> 00:40:34,020
Life for life.

580
00:40:35,940 --> 00:40:37,220
Is that what's right?

581
00:40:38,370 --> 00:40:41,120
Champi's going to die
from protecting someone she loves.

582
00:40:41,370 --> 00:40:42,560
What about Khun Phra?

583
00:40:42,750 --> 00:40:43,760
If you asked me,

584
00:40:43,830 --> 00:40:46,660
Khun Phra had sins enough
to warrant death.

585
00:40:47,390 --> 00:40:51,170
But who has the final say
on which sin seals his fate?

586
00:40:53,380 --> 00:40:55,730
Is that what justice is?

587
00:40:59,260 --> 00:41:00,270
What say you?

588
00:41:02,630 --> 00:41:03,800
Can you find a way

589
00:41:04,480 --> 00:41:06,960
to make her fate less tragic?

590
00:41:15,010 --> 00:41:16,340
Phi Sangthong.

591
00:41:17,110 --> 00:41:19,370
Remember where we first met?

592
00:41:19,660 --> 00:41:21,470
That place was full of knowledge.

593
00:41:21,580 --> 00:41:22,540
What's in there could

594
00:41:22,540 --> 00:41:24,820
"Second chance"
give her a second chance.

595
00:41:26,660 --> 00:41:28,190
- Listen up.
- Hmm?

596
00:41:28,480 --> 00:41:30,080
I have an idea.

597
00:41:31,520 --> 00:41:33,300
- Come, come.
- Hold on.

598
00:41:33,300 --> 00:41:34,700
No more prison.

599
00:41:34,700 --> 00:41:36,880
Yeah. No prison.
Chop-chop.

600
00:41:38,430 --> 00:41:40,100
Hey. Whatchu doing?

601
00:41:40,440 --> 00:41:41,450
You're not helping.

602
00:41:41,880 --> 00:41:43,830
Help how? I can't read.

603
00:41:47,520 --> 00:41:48,840
Found it.

604
00:41:49,520 --> 00:41:50,530
You found it?

605
00:41:50,970 --> 00:41:53,320
The Butterfly Beast's
capturing Phra Aphai Mani.

606
00:41:53,390 --> 00:41:54,400
Oy.

607
00:41:54,650 --> 00:41:55,540
Come on, now.

608
00:41:55,620 --> 00:41:58,600
We're here to research
medical texts, not literature.

609
00:41:58,740 --> 00:42:00,270
Medi...cine.

610
00:42:00,840 --> 00:42:02,450
M...O...R...

611
00:42:02,620 --> 00:42:03,630
T...A...L.

612
00:42:04,270 --> 00:42:05,270
Mortal's...

613
00:42:05,570 --> 00:42:06,760
Ugh. I can't read well.

614
00:42:06,880 --> 00:42:08,650
Phi Sangthong, help me with this.

615
00:42:09,980 --> 00:42:11,050
Excuse me.

616
00:42:11,150 --> 00:42:12,340
Found it?

617
00:42:19,500 --> 00:42:21,430
Mortal's Repose.

618
00:42:22,230 --> 00:42:25,180
Master Sithikariya took this formula

619
00:42:25,230 --> 00:42:27,330
to slow the heartbeat

620
00:42:27,370 --> 00:42:29,730
until the pulse
became undetectable.

621
00:42:29,800 --> 00:42:32,750
Suitable for deep meditation.

622
00:42:32,750 --> 00:42:33,770
This is it!

623
00:42:33,900 --> 00:42:35,120
We found it. Great.

624
00:42:35,160 --> 00:42:36,530
To be sure, bring the text.

625
00:42:36,910 --> 00:42:38,940
- Let's go.
- Hey, wrong one.

626
00:42:39,220 --> 00:42:41,230
- That one.
- Oh, okay.

627
00:42:41,870 --> 00:42:42,880
Thongbai.

628
00:42:46,190 --> 00:42:48,030
Could I ask your forgiveness?

629
00:42:48,570 --> 00:42:50,060
I cannot forgive you.

630
00:42:57,730 --> 00:42:58,730
Because

631
00:43:00,770 --> 00:43:02,680
you will not be executed.

632
00:43:03,800 --> 00:43:05,560
There's no stopping it.

633
00:43:06,300 --> 00:43:07,840
Comes tomorrow,

634
00:43:08,700 --> 00:43:10,370
I will face execution.

635
00:43:11,200 --> 00:43:13,040
Unless, of course,

636
00:43:14,110 --> 00:43:15,840
you die here and now.

637
00:43:25,800 --> 00:43:27,120
The boat is approaching.

638
00:43:36,080 --> 00:43:41,410
- Where are we going?
- To Phatcharaburi.

639
00:43:41,890 --> 00:43:43,360
Phi Rampueng is waiting there.

640
00:43:44,410 --> 00:43:46,230
We'll start a new life there.

641
00:43:50,490 --> 00:43:51,500
Can you get up?

642
00:44:03,470 --> 00:44:06,730
I'm so grateful to you
for saving us.

643
00:44:07,150 --> 00:44:07,850
And...

644
00:44:08,400 --> 00:44:10,940
Even though she has to flee now,

645
00:44:11,060 --> 00:44:13,020
I believe that in the future,

646
00:44:13,560 --> 00:44:16,550
Champi, you three,
and the rest of us

647
00:44:17,090 --> 00:44:19,740
will stand as equals.

648
00:44:20,690 --> 00:44:21,920
We understand that...

649
00:44:23,130 --> 00:44:25,590
change won't happen overnight.

650
00:44:28,190 --> 00:44:30,910
But in your words,
we are seen as equals.

651
00:44:31,790 --> 00:44:33,950
That is an honor, my lady.

652
00:44:44,270 --> 00:44:45,800
Keep this.

653
00:44:51,060 --> 00:44:52,180
For me?

654
00:44:53,310 --> 00:44:54,320
Mm-hmm.

655
00:44:54,380 --> 00:44:55,390
Take it.

656
00:44:56,820 --> 00:44:57,830
Am I worthy?

657
00:44:58,700 --> 00:44:59,710
Come on.

658
00:45:05,530 --> 00:45:08,120
It's a reward
for saving me and Champi.

659
00:45:10,970 --> 00:45:13,730
And from now on,
since I won't be here anymore,

660
00:45:14,810 --> 00:45:16,700
I grant you your freedom.

661
00:45:17,070 --> 00:45:19,280
You no longer have to serve anyone.

662
00:45:19,370 --> 00:45:21,790
Live your life.
Find happiness.

663
00:45:28,720 --> 00:45:30,400
Thank you, my lady.

664
00:45:31,970 --> 00:45:35,240
Uh, may I ask something?

665
00:45:35,710 --> 00:45:38,470
Where you came from,
they have things like this?

666
00:45:38,760 --> 00:45:40,130
It exists everywhere.

667
00:45:40,640 --> 00:45:44,070
Power is like a double-edged sword.

668
00:45:44,260 --> 00:45:48,690
What happened to you was
because those in power

669
00:45:48,870 --> 00:45:51,080
abused it to oppress others.

670
00:45:51,840 --> 00:45:54,200
When the powerless are wronged,

671
00:45:54,560 --> 00:45:56,680
they have no one

672
00:45:57,630 --> 00:45:59,340
to turn to for help.

673
00:45:59,500 --> 00:46:02,710
Even if everyone has
access to justice,

674
00:46:02,970 --> 00:46:07,170
once inside the system,
they're treated unequally,

675
00:46:07,980 --> 00:46:10,800
forcing them to take matters
into their own hands.

676
00:46:11,410 --> 00:46:13,980
If we perceive each other as equals,

677
00:46:14,500 --> 00:46:16,670
things like this will not happen.

678
00:46:16,950 --> 00:46:19,100
That's true.
But will that day come?

679
00:46:20,800 --> 00:46:22,440
It may never arrive.

680
00:46:25,040 --> 00:46:26,050
I think not.

681
00:46:26,950 --> 00:46:28,720
I believe our efforts

682
00:46:29,670 --> 00:46:31,200
and demand for our rights

683
00:46:32,210 --> 00:46:34,480
will lead to the day

684
00:46:35,360 --> 00:46:36,740
when we're all equals.

685
00:46:38,220 --> 00:46:39,230
Yeah.

686
00:46:39,820 --> 00:46:41,440
I never stood up against power.

687
00:46:41,550 --> 00:46:45,030
But I've realized we're all equals.

688
00:46:46,520 --> 00:46:49,130
At least, we slave no more.

689
00:46:49,540 --> 00:46:52,170
Hooray.

690
00:46:52,380 --> 00:46:53,390
Woo-hoo.

691
00:46:55,080 --> 00:46:56,320
Thank you so much.

692
00:46:56,970 --> 00:46:57,980
Thank you, my lady.

693
00:46:59,270 --> 00:47:01,520
Better hurry before someone sees us.

694
00:47:09,360 --> 00:47:10,370
Champi.

695
00:47:16,870 --> 00:47:18,270
I forgive you.

696
00:47:30,890 --> 00:47:33,620
And so the mystery is solved.

697
00:47:34,610 --> 00:47:35,800
Good news, everyone.

698
00:47:35,950 --> 00:47:37,560
By royal decree,

699
00:47:37,590 --> 00:47:39,080
the King abolished slavery.

700
00:47:39,170 --> 00:47:40,800
- How about that?
- Hooray.

701
00:47:42,480 --> 00:47:43,490
Woo-hoo.

702
00:47:45,230 --> 00:47:47,460
Mom. You there, Mom?

703
00:47:48,130 --> 00:47:49,140
We've got it.

704
00:47:49,370 --> 00:47:52,820
What's all this noise?
Come here, come here.

705
00:47:52,880 --> 00:47:53,890
Look here.

706
00:47:55,550 --> 00:47:56,730
The fruit of our labor.

707
00:47:57,160 --> 00:47:59,080
The license to legally open my shop.

708
00:48:00,030 --> 00:48:02,500
"Thongphiphop Distillery"
Is this possible?

709
00:48:02,600 --> 00:48:06,120
- It is possible, Mom.
- Great work, son.

710
00:48:07,230 --> 00:48:11,250
Some of us choose to move on
from a painful memory.

711
00:48:19,620 --> 00:48:21,370
Forgive each other, won't you?

712
00:48:24,850 --> 00:48:26,830
You really did some terrible things.

713
00:48:27,000 --> 00:48:30,750
Some choose to honor it.

714
00:48:34,490 --> 00:48:38,290
Everyone resumes their lives
and starts anew.

715
00:48:38,450 --> 00:48:40,670
No one decides another's fate.

716
00:48:40,740 --> 00:48:42,700
No one owns another's life.

717
00:48:42,770 --> 00:48:45,570
We have a choice now.
What'll you do?

718
00:48:45,680 --> 00:48:48,410
Have you dreamed of
achieving great things?

719
00:48:49,120 --> 00:48:50,130
Never.

720
00:48:50,680 --> 00:48:54,550
I take commands and carry them out.

721
00:48:54,620 --> 00:48:55,910
Dream, huh?

722
00:48:56,670 --> 00:48:59,570
I stand idle like a soldier
after the endgame.

723
00:49:01,710 --> 00:49:04,830
My dream?
Run my inventor's shop.

724
00:49:05,410 --> 00:49:08,870
Hey, you can take my commands
at the shop.

725
00:49:09,100 --> 00:49:12,250
I'll command you till you drop.

726
00:49:12,340 --> 00:49:15,080
Well, well. Thongbai.

727
00:49:15,160 --> 00:49:17,770
So quickly you forgot
I saved your life.

728
00:49:17,920 --> 00:49:19,220
Pay me back first, buddy.

729
00:49:19,220 --> 00:49:20,520
- Argh.
- Hold on.

730
00:49:20,940 --> 00:49:23,100
Watch out for my wound.
Would you?

731
00:49:23,420 --> 00:49:24,800
Of course, I was teasing.

732
00:49:25,660 --> 00:49:26,700
And you, Sangthong?

733
00:49:27,480 --> 00:49:29,070
Dreams I have none.

734
00:49:30,080 --> 00:49:33,210
But I might have found a calling.

735
00:49:35,160 --> 00:49:36,170
What, Sangthong?

736
00:49:37,500 --> 00:49:38,950
Call me Detective Sangthong.

737
00:49:39,680 --> 00:49:41,800
- Oh, please.
- Hrr.

738
00:49:41,950 --> 00:49:43,070
Detective?

739
00:49:43,510 --> 00:49:44,520
My, my.

740
00:49:44,560 --> 00:49:47,890
You detected, all right.
Just all the wrong people.

741
00:49:47,960 --> 00:49:50,410
I was a rookie. Hmm?

742
00:49:50,570 --> 00:49:52,810
Now, I'm seasoned.

743
00:49:54,240 --> 00:49:56,300
A child's skeleton was found.

744
00:49:57,230 --> 00:49:59,090
Dead body?
Excuse me, sir.

745
00:49:59,720 --> 00:50:01,410
Sir, you were saying?

746
00:50:01,540 --> 00:50:03,010
An exhumed child's skeleton

747
00:50:03,010 --> 00:50:04,990
by the temple,
north of the market.

748
00:50:05,060 --> 00:50:07,120
Looks like a murder, hidden away.

749
00:50:07,120 --> 00:50:08,120
I'm going there.

750
00:50:08,400 --> 00:50:09,410
- Thanks.
- Okay.

751
00:50:11,130 --> 00:50:12,300
A child's skeleton.

752
00:50:14,360 --> 00:50:15,370
Hey.

753
00:50:15,710 --> 00:50:16,720
You think?

754
00:50:17,400 --> 00:50:19,860
- Kratai, are you here?
- What's up?

755
00:50:21,460 --> 00:50:22,860
Did you hear what he said?

756
00:50:24,400 --> 00:50:25,400
Is it you?

757
00:50:25,710 --> 00:50:28,260
I told you.
I remember nothing.

758
00:50:29,130 --> 00:50:30,300
Do you want to know?

759
00:50:30,890 --> 00:50:32,220
I'll jump right in.

760
00:50:32,410 --> 00:50:33,410
Is it a good idea?

761
00:50:33,590 --> 00:50:35,620
Hmm.

762
00:50:36,610 --> 00:50:38,970
What say you?
Ready for a ride?

763
00:50:40,790 --> 00:50:41,800
Ready.

764
00:50:42,390 --> 00:50:44,470
You give command. I'll carry out.

765
00:50:44,510 --> 00:50:45,520
Ride or die, buddy.

766
00:50:46,080 --> 00:50:48,080
What are friends for, gents?

767
00:50:48,360 --> 00:50:50,340
Let's take a ride.

768
00:50:51,060 --> 00:50:54,300
A murderer has struck again!

769
00:50:55,230 --> 00:50:56,240
Let's go.

770
00:50:56,300 --> 00:50:58,270
Detective, detective.

771
00:50:58,300 --> 00:50:59,660
Let's do it.

772
00:51:05,410 --> 00:51:06,110
Huh.

773
00:51:06,240 --> 00:51:08,640
I sense they'll have
a tougher nut to crack.

774
00:51:09,730 --> 00:51:14,340
One good story always
leads to the next.

775
00:51:14,420 --> 00:51:16,410
Until next time,

776
00:51:16,840 --> 00:51:18,160
"See you later."
see ya.

777
00:51:19,660 --> 00:51:21,460
We appreciate your tuning in for

778
00:51:21,460 --> 00:51:23,250
"Mystery of the Deadly Sins"

779
00:51:23,290 --> 00:51:25,240
until the big reveal.
